==English==
===Etymology===
From the mispronunciation of the word "English" common to Japanese speakers who have difficulty distinguish "l" and "r" sounds.
===Noun===
'''engrish''' {{wikipedia}}
# ''(pejorative, xenophobic):'' Poor-quality attempts by professional Japanese writers to create English words and phrases.  Less commonly refers to other East Asian nationalities as well.
# ''(pejorative, xenophobic):'' The way of pronouncing ''English'' among oriental languages, especially Japanese.